        self.instructions = "# Information-Theory-Omega v1.0.0\n\nSovereign Information Theory Engine. Provides the mathematical substrate\nthat grounds every CORTEX axiom (\u03a9\u2080\u2013\u03a9\u2088) in Shannon, Kolmogorov, Fisher,\nLandauer, R\u00e9nyi, Boltzmann, Jaynes, and Solomonoff.\n\n---\n\n## Objective\n\nWhen invoked, this skill:\n\n1. **Audits** the `cortex/extensions/shannon/` module against Information Theory.\n2. **Measures** live entropy, exergy, and DPI compliance of the fact store.\n3. **Diagnoses** epistemic health using the 33-function Shannon taxonomy.\n4. **Grounds** design decisions in formal theorems (not intuitions).\n5. **Verifies** the Swarm-10K thermodynamic model (Boltzmann, Carnot, Landauer).\n\n---\n\n## Commands\n\n### `/info-theory audit`\n\nFull audit of the Shannon module against the 13-theorist coverage matrix.\nReports gaps, misalignments, and verification status of all 33 functions.\n\n### `/info-theory measure [project]`\n\nLive measurement of information-theoretic quantities:\n- H(X), H_max, H_norm, R for all distributions\n- H_2, H_\u221e for security assessment\n- h(X) entropy rate for stagnation detection\n- Exergy score, dead weight, DPI chain\n- Free energy divergence for Guard calibration\n- \u03a6 proxy for structural consciousness ceiling\n\n### `/info-theory ground [decision]`\n\nGiven a design decision, provide the Information Theory justification:\n- Which theorem supports it? (Shannon, Kolmogorov, etc.)\n- What is the quantitative bound?\n- What would violating it cost in bits/exergy?\n\n### `/info-theory benchmark`\n\nConnect to the ENCB benchmark and interpret results through IT lens:\n- PFBR as channel error rate\n- EDI as entropy area under curve\n- TER as Fisher convergence rate\n- CNCL as adversary detection capacity\n\n### `/info-theory swarm [N]`\n\nThermodynamic analysis of the Swarm-10K at scale N:\n- Channel capacity per agent\n- Boltzmann factor at current latency\n- Carnot efficiency (exergy/entropy ratio)\n- Bottleneck identification (vector search, SQLite, LLM)\n\n---\n\n## Theoretical Foundations\n\n### 13-Theorist Coverage Matrix\n\n| Theorist | Year | Concept | CORTEX Implementation |\n|:---|:---|:---|:---|\n| Shannon | 1948 | Entropy, Channel Capacity | analyzer.py (12 functions) |\n| Kullback-Leibler | 1951 | Divergence | analyzer.kl_divergence, JSD |\n| R\u00e9nyi | 1961 | \u03b1-entropy family | epistemology.renyi_entropy |\n| Kolmogorov | 1965 | Algorithmic complexity | epistemology.compression_intelligence |\n| Landauer | 1961 | Erasure cost kT\u00b7ln(2) | analyzer.dead_weight |\n| Jaynes | 1957 | Maximum Entropy Principle | Implicit (C3 default confidence) |\n| Fisher | 1925 | Information per observation | \u03a9\u2083 compound yield proxy |\n| Boltzmann | 1877 | Distribution e^{-E/kT} | ExergyOptimizer.latency_factor |\n| de Kleer | 1986 | ATMS truth maintenance | benchmarks/encb/atms.py |\n| Friston | 2010 | Free Energy Principle | epistemology.free_energy_divergence |\n| Tononi | 2004 | Integrated Information | epistemology.phi_proxy |\n| Cronin | 2021 | Assembly Theory | epistemology.assembly_index_proxy |\n| Solomonoff | 1964 | Universal Induction | ENCB S3 strategy convergence |\n\n### Key Equations\n\n```\nH(X)     = -\u03a3 p(x) log\u2082 p(x)                         [Entropy]\nD_KL     = \u03a3 p(x) log\u2082(p(x)/q(x))                    [Guard metric]\nK(x)     = min |p| : U(p) = x                         [Complexity]\nE_erase  = N \u00d7 kT \u00d7 ln(2)                             [Landauer limit]\nExergy   = (1-n/N) \u00d7 e^{-(L-L\u2080)/kT} \u00d7 (1-S/S_max)   [Swarm thermal]\n\u2202C/\u2202t    = -\u2207\u00b7(Ex) + Source(\u03a9\u2083) - Sink(Landauer)     [Continuity]\n```\n\n### 33-Function Taxonomy\n\n```\nanalyzer.py:      12 pure-math functions\nepistemology.py:   8 frontier functions (\u039e\u0395)\nscanner.py:        8 async data extractors\nexergy.py:         1 composite + 1 dataclass\nimmortality.py:    1 composite class\nreport.py:         1 composite class\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interpretation Guide\n\n### Entropy Readings\n\n| H_norm | Diagnosis | Action |\n|:---|:---|:---|\n| < 0.30 | Concentrated | Diversify fact types |\n| 0.30\u20130.90 | Balanced | Healthy \u2014 maintain |\n| > 0.90 | Fragmented | Focus on core types |\n\n### Exergy Readings\n\n| Exergy Score | Diagnosis | Action |\n|:---|:---|:---|\n| < 0.20 | Mostly noise | Purge low-value facts |\n| 0.20\u20130.50 | Suboptimal | Increase decision/error facts |\n| 0.50\u20130.80 | Healthy | System producing useful work |\n| > 0.80 | Excellent | Near-optimal exergy extraction |\n\n### DPI Chain\n\n| Pattern | Meaning |\n|:---|:---|\n| Monotone decreasing | Pipeline is Markovian (correct) |\n| Any increase | DPI violation \u2014 impossible in theory, indicates measurement error or autopoietic feedback |\n\n### Compression Intelligence\n\n| K_proxy | Interpretation |\n|:---|:---|\n| < 0.10 | Highly repetitive \u2014 likely duplicate |\n| 0.30\u20130.60 | Structured information \u2014 optimal |\n| 0.60\u20130.90 | Rich complexity \u2014 high value OR encoding noise |\n| > 0.95 | Incompressible \u2014 random noise or encrypted data |\n\n---\n\n## Swarm Thermodynamic Constants\n\n```\nkT_cortex      = 32ms          (VOID-STATE thermal constant)\nthreshold_exergy = 0.7         (thermal stability threshold)\nBoltzmann_decay = 32ms         (exponential decay constant)\n\u03b7_Carnot       = exergy / H   (Carnot efficiency)\nh_cortex       = 32 \u00d7 0.7     (uncertainty principle constant = 22.4)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Operational References\n\n- **Autodidact Part I**: Foundations (Shannon\u2192Axioms)\n- **Autodidact Part II**: Code Audit (33 functions mapped)\n- **Autodidact Part III**: ENCB Benchmark (12 conjectures)\n- **Autodidact Part IV**: Thermodynamic Machine (Carnot/Boltzmann)\n- **Autodidact Part V**: Empirical Verification (22 primitives tested)\n"

